Abstrak:
At 4:55 a.m. California time on 15 September, hundreds of scientists watched their life’s work go up in flames. The Cassini spacecraft disintegrated in Saturn’s atmosphere in a mission-ending move meant
to keep the probe from contaminating any of the planet’s moons, including Titan and Enceladus, that could harbour signs of life
